          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The Kr and Xe precursors of Rb and Cs isotopes are",
                "  retained within the target and decay there. Therefore",
                "  the yields measured for Rb and Cs isotopes are cumu-",
                "  lative. Since independent yields of Rb isotopes below",
                "  A=93 and of Cs isotopes below A=143 (see Exfor30960)",
                "  are a small fraction of their cumulative yields, it",
                "  was not possible to calculate them with reasonable",
                "  accuracy. Instead, the obtained cumulative yields are",
                "  presented here.",
                "Comments by compiler:",
                "  The independent yields from this experiment and more",
                "  details are given in exfor30960. The information on",
                "  the cumulative yields is very brief and in Hebrew. It",
                "  is assumed that the sample and method were the same",
                "  as in Exfor30960 and are partly reproduced here.",
                "No information is given on analysis, error analysis and",
                "  how absolute yields were obtained (monitor).",
                "  However, the yields (not the errors]) for Rb-91 and",
                "  Cs-139 are identical to literature values shown in",
                "  Table 9 of IA-1345."
              ]
            }
          ],
